During their visit to China, President Donald Trump and First Lady Melania Trump participated in various cultural activities and events. They attended an arrival ceremony, had a welcome tea, and had a tour at the Forbidden City with President Xi and Madame Peng. The First Lady also visited Banchang Primary School, where she participated in classes such as Peking opera, astronomy, fashion and design, calligraphy, cooking, and Chinese architecture. She then attended a U.S. Embassy meet-and-greet and ended the day with a state dinner and cultural performance at the Great Hall of the People. On day three, Mrs. Trump visited the panda exhibit at the Beijing Zoo and toured the Great Wall. She expressed her gratitude towards President Xi and Madame Peng for their hospitality and believed that both countries made great progress during the trip. She also expressed her anticipation for future visits.